Global Automotive Manual Service Disconnect (MSD) Market Insights
Automotive Manual Service Disconnect (MSD) Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 9.8% from 2024 to 2030.

Automotive Manual Service Disconnect (MSD) Market Overview
The global Automotive Manual Service Disconnect (MSD) market was valued at approximately USD 5.2 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow at a CAGR of 6.3% over the forecast period. This growth is driven by increasing automotive safety standards, advancements in electric vehicle technologies, and a growing demand for more reliable and efficient vehicle maintenance solutions. The market encompasses the integration of manual service disconnects in vehicles to ensure safety during service and repair procedures. The increasing prevalence of electric and hybrid vehicles is expected to boost the market as these vehicles require specialized safety equipment like MSD systems to avoid accidents during maintenance. As the automotive industry continues to evolve with technological innovations, the demand for advanced MSD systems is anticipated to rise substantially in the coming years.

